Remsen Street, east of Hicks Street, showing in the center, the home of John A. Latimer (No. 63), who was an accountant for the Brooklyn Savings Bank in 1876.

About 1900.

Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.

Hicks Street, west side, south of Remsen Street. The corner building is the William G. Low home, and beyond it is the Grace (P.E.) Church.

1922.

Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.

71-79 Remsen Street, north side, between Hicks and Henry Streets, showing the Thomas Sullivan residence (No. 77), facing the street lamp. (He was president of the Brooklyn City R.R. Co. for many years).

1922.
